  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6 and boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel the <strong>butternut squash</strong> and cut in half using a sharp knife, then scoop out the seeds with a spoon and discard</p><p>Tip: Drizzle the knife with vegetable oil for easier chopping</p><p>Chop<strong> half </strong>of the <strong>butternut squash</strong> into 8 <span class=\"text-danger\">[16]</span> wedges</p><p>Cut the<strong> remaining butternut squash</strong> into bite-sized cubes</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1602248526363-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1602248526363-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1602248526363-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1602248526363-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1602248526363-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> butternut squash wedges</strong> and <strong>butternut squash cubes </strong>to a tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min or until softened</p><p>Whilst the squash is cooking, add the<strong> tortiglioni</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water </strong>with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> </strong>tortiglioni<strong> </strong>for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1602248539085-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1602248539085-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1602248539085-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1602248539085-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1602248539085-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>in 250ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [500ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> then add 100ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [200ml]</span> <strong>milk </strong>and give it a good mix up</p><p>Chop <strong>basil </strong>roughly, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1602248555957-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1602248555957-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1602248555957-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1602248555957-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1602248555957-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the tortiglioni is cooked, drain and keep in the sieve until later, reserve the pot</p><p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat with a generous knob of <strong>butter </strong>and a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Once the butter has melted, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and cook for 1 min</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1602248608593-x200.jpg",
